<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="343" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[98,803,140,1544]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">
Tubers 2-5, ovoid to globose, entire
<emphasis box="[506,510,1105,1128]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Leaves narrow, canalicu­ late, acute, entire, usually shiny
<emphasis box="[471,475,1133,1156]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Flowers in a spike
<emphasis box="[714,718,1133,1156]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Outer perianth-segments ovate-lanceolate, acute, partially connate, connivent with the linear-lanceolate, acuminate inner lateral to form a galea
<emphasis box="[242,246,1216,1239]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Labellum large, constricted into basal hypochile, with two indistinct lateral lobes, and prominent, pendent epichile
<emphasis box="[797,801,1243,1266]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Spur absent
<emphasis box="[235,239,1271,1294]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Column long
<emphasis box="[406,410,1271,1294]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Rostellum small
<emphasis box="[612,616,1271,1294]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
Viscidium soli­ tary; bursicle simple
<emphasis box="[324,328,1299,1322]" pageId="18" pageNumber="343">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
